Reasoning: The paper investigates the public perception of AI by analyzing data shared on Twitter, which involves natural language processing and sentiment analysis. Therefore, the most likely sub-category is cs.SI (Social and Information Networks). Additionally, the paper also involves analyzing the language used in tweets, which falls under the sub-category of cs.CL (Computation and Language). The paper also touches upon the ethical and societal implications of AI, which could fall under the sub-categories of cs.CY (Computers and Society) and cs.CE (Computational Engineering, Finance, and Science). Finally, the paper also involves analyzing the behavior and emotions of Twitter users, which could fall under the sub-category of cs.HC (Human-Computer Interaction).
